\cf2 	6. Styles\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\slleading30\sa320
\cf2 Styles are the method of rendering geospatial data. Styles for GeoServer are written in Styled Layer Descriptor (SLD), a subset of XML. Please see the section on {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://docs.geoserver.org/stable/en/user/styling/index.html#styling"}}{\fldrslt Styling}} for more information on working with styles.\
On this page, you can register or create a new style, edit an existing style, or delete remove a style.\
\pard\pardeftab720\slleading30\sa300
\cf2 Edit Styles\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\slleading30\sa320
\cf2 The Style Editor page presents options for configuring a style\'92s name and code. SLD names are specified at the top in the name field. Typing or pasting of SLD code can be done in one of two modes. The first mode is an embedded {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.cdolivet.com/index.php?page=editArea"}}{\fldrslt \ul \ulc4 EditArea}} a rich editor. The second mode alternate mode is an unformatted text editor. Check the Toggle Editor to switch between modes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\slleading30
\cf2 \
The rich editor is designed for text formatting, search and replace, line numbering, and real-time syntax highlighting. You can also switch view to full-screen mode for a larger editing area.\
\
